Costume->Material Palette

Material Palette..is the next selection found in the "Costume" menu.

Material Palette Editor contains the following selections in its menu
:

File, Edit, Palettes.

File : Menu is used to load a new palette into the editor. Generally
there are a number of basic materials available as defaults.

Edit : This menu contains "Cut", "Copy", "Paste" and "Delete" options.
When a material is edited/created in this editor, it has to be
"copied", so it can be accessed in the main material editor to set
material for the selected object.

Palettes: This menu lists all the palettes of materials that are
shipped with the system. Material from a palette may be selected and
modified in the Material Palette Editor and when this material setting
is "copied", it may be pasted onto the selected material in the
material editor.

This option is not available in this release.
